No cheating. Pick your dessert, then look to see what psychiatrists think about you! After taking this dessert personality test, send this e-mail on to others, but when you do, be sure to put your choice of dessert in the subject line. ALSO, SEND IT TO THE PERSON WHO SENT IT TO YOU! 

If all of the desserts listed below were sitting in front of you, which would you choose? (Sorry, you can only pick one!) 

Angel Food 
Brownies 
Lemon Meringue 
Vanilla Cake/Chocolate Icing 
Strawberry Short Cake 
Chocolate Cake/Chocolate Icing 
Ice Cream 
Carrot Cake 

NO .. You can't change your mind once you scroll down! So think carefully what your choice will be! 

OK - Now that you've made your choice, this is what research says about you: 


Angel food - Sweet, loving, cuddly. You love all warm and fuzzy items.. A little nutty at times. Sometimes you need an ice cream cone at the end of the day. Others perceive you as being childlike and immature at times. 

Brownies - You are adventurous, love new ideas, are a champion of underdogs and a slayer of dragons. When tempers flare up, you whip out your saber. You are always the oddball with a unique sense of humor and direction. You tend to be very loyal. 

Lemon Meringue - Smooth, sexy, &articulate with your hands, you are an excellent after-dinner speaker and a good teacher. But don't try to 
walk and chew gum at the same time. A bit of a diva at times, but you have many friends. 

Vanilla Cake/Chocolate Icing - Fun-loving, sassy, humorous. Not very grounded in life; very indecisive and lack motivation. Everyone enjoys 
being around you, but you are a practical joker. Others should be cautious in making you mad. However, you are a friend for life. 

Strawberry Short Cake - Romantic, warm, loving. You care about other people and can be counted on in a pinch. You tend to melt. You can be 
overly emotional and annoying at times.

Chocolate Cake/Chocolate Icing - Sexy, always ready to give and receive. Very creative, adventurous, ambitious, and passionate. You have a 
cold exterior but are warm on the inside. Not afraid to take chances. Will not settle for anything average in life. Love to laugh. 

Ice Cream - You like sports, whether it be baseball, football, basketball, or soccer. If you could, you would like to participate, but you enjoy watching sports. You don't like to give up the remote control. You tend to be self-centered and high maintenance. 

Carrot Cake - You are a very fun loving person, who likes to laugh. You are fun to be with. People like to hang out with you. You are a very warm hearted person and a little quirky at times. You have many loyal friends.

wow ... camping was sooo much fun! i wanna go back.. here's my story:

FRIDAY: Me britt and leagh drove to Hartford, Ny a.k.a. "HICK-VILLE" only farms are there! lmao! and you have to drive a million miles to get somewhere lol... ok.. we get there at like 11 at nite and we have to put the tent up in the dark! WHAT A TASK! we dont know how to put tents up! so earlier me n leagh were talking and leagh was like im gunna miss the fighting in my house and as soon as we got there this guy kenny was like "stop poking me with the fucking stick asshole b4 i shove it up your ass!" and i was like u are gunna fit in perfectly!

SATURDAY:  We woke up to some asshole kids throwing catterpillers on our tent!!! there were hundreds!!!We chilled at the campsite! then we dicided to go to the ice cream shop. it took use like an hour to get there! i got all blisters from britts crappy sandals!lmao.. then we decided to go to the stream... we had to cut through a farm to get to it and we ran into barbed wire! omg i thought it was like TEXAS CHAINSAW MASSACRE! if i heard a chain saw i was bookin it! so we reached to stream and decided to go back through the woods! bad idea! we were crossing this badly overgrown field and some turkey scared the shit outta me and flew! so we were walking through the woods where we got lost and found somemore barbed wire! so britt called her mom from the cell fone! (see we arent stupid like those kids on the blair witch project!) and we followed the gunshots cuz the guys do shooting games there...and we actually found our way outta the woods!!!! it was amazing .... and then i herd Kenny listening to Godsmack so me n leagh werelike GODSMACK!!! and he was like yea they are good and i was like yea they are amazing!!! and Kenny's bro lives in california and is in a band and hangs out with godsmack and metallica and all those people and was like ill get you guys autographs!!! and we were soo excited!!!! i love kenny and dave!!!!p.s. britt slept the whole day today!

SUNDAY: We woke up and got dressed then me n leagh were taking a walk and were talking about how we were gunna meet godsmack and metallica one day and marry them!! i love leagh!
so we were supposed to go to town and so we were just chillen and waiting and watching kenny and dave shoot ... and got totally sunburned!!!! ong im soo red.. wait till tuesday! we went to town and were go-cart racing and i spun leagh out and dave spun me out!!! the guy yelled at us saying not to bump! FUCK YOU! lol.. then we went to town and took a tour of this alien place where they scared the shit outta me,britt, and brooke!!! lmao!!! it was scarry!!! today dave and kenny were funny! me n leagh were pissing ourselves!

MONDAY: OUr leaving day.. depressed.. those three days went by soo fast! IM GOING TO MISS EVERYONE!!!! I CANT WAIT TILL NEXT YEAR!

1. im supposed to be a college student on a front porch after a big meal who needs to make a big decision... here it goes...

I DO :by amanda tomasco

"Will you marry me, Danielle" are the words that are ringing in my head. I had a month off, then graduation and i am earning a bachelor's degree in Pre-Med. My life is just starting out! What am I going to do?
   Jon and I had been dating all throughout college. I love him and he loves me.. that sort of thing. For our vacation, he and I are traveling to louisiana. "i cant wait for you to meet my parents!' jon said in excitement. I was excited and nervous all at the same time. Im just a small new england girl from_______(i need a city). "i dont know if i can remember all the names of your family' i said nervously. "dont worry Dan, youll do fine." Jon said with a smile on his face.
   As the plane landed, I felt this weird feeling in the pit of my stomach. Something is going to happen. I dont know if it is good or bad. We drove up the long , dirt driveway. I have never been on a real farm. "this is amazing JOn. You grew up here??" "yea! but dont let it deceive you though. It is a lot of work!" As we walked up to the front door I went over the list of names in my head. "Father-Dave, Mom- JoAnn, Brother-James, and sister-Karen"
    'JON! You're home!" screamed JoAnn, his mom. "oh look at our little boy ! And this must be Danielle. Come in come in" His mom was the perfect image of a mother , hair neately pinned back and an apron on over it. As i greeted each family member it seemed like they were perfect. Dave, his father, was just what a farmer should look like, a scruffy 5 o'clock shadow, a cotton flannel shirt, and jeans. "hi danielle, how are ya? Im Dave" he said in a deep voice. "im fine glad to be here finally" i said as i sat on one side of the couch. Just then i herd poundingsof feet. A boy and girl ran down the stairs. "That must be James and Karen" jon said to me as he sat down next to me. "kids go see Jon!" JoAnn said from the kitchen. The aroma that came from that room smelt like we were in a five star resturant. Jon's sister Karen must have been at least 10 years old. She rean up to Jon and gave him a big hug. "JON! I mised you!" She said as her bouncy blonde curls covered jons face. "I missed you too!, Karen this is Danielle." Jon said. I smiled and said hello. "HI" she said... "do you like Kenny chesney?" "Ummm.. actually i do " i said with a laugh. James must have been 13 or 14 because he just sat dowm playing Donkey Kong on his gameboy. "hey James " Jon said "Hey" he repllied. "kids these days" jon said . Dave, Jon, and I all laughed. "dinner! Joann screamed from the dining room.
   did you kids wash your hands?" Joann said to them."yes mommy! see??" Karen said loudly. "how about you? James?" "yea ma" he said. We all sat around the large dining room table. Sitting on the table looked like the most delicious foon I have ever seen! Stuffed turkey, peas, carrots, and apple pie! my favorite! We ate until our stomachs were about to burst. just as i finished jon stood up, tapping his glass. "Um everyone, I have a very improtant question." he walked quickly over to me and kneeled on one knee. "Danielle, will you marry me??!" he said nervously as he pulled out the diamond ring. There was a lump in my throat. I was speechless. "i...uhh...umm" "oh.. how romantic" joann said as they awaited my answer. "I think I need some air" I said and ran to the porch.
   Those words are repeating and repeating in my head. "Im not ready for this, but i love jon , but im only 23 years old." Not knowing what to say, I slowly walked in. Their eyes starred wondering what i would say. Jon ran over. "Jon I love you" "I love you too" he quickly replied. "Let me finish" I said "I love you but i cant marry you. "im too young  and i have my whole life ahead of me." I looked down to the hardwood floor and kicked some dust around.
